OL,7,FThe defendant said he had not been to
OL,8,FLondon since a 2016 visit to
OL,9,FBuckingham Palace stables.
OL,11,FInsisting that the packages he sent
OL,12,Fdid not amount to stalking, he told
OL,13,Fthe court: "Stalkers want things and
OL,14,Fblackmail, whereas ordinary
OL,15,Fgentlemanly types just give gifts for
OL,16,Fno particular reason sometimes.
OL,18,F"I haven't been to London for years. I
OL,19,Fdidn't take it as the definition of
OL,20,Fstalking, just sending things."
